<item>
            <title>[LU-74] An OSC lock is not cancelled if a process is killed while lock is ungranted</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-74</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Oracle testing has uncovered a problem with the way CLIO + LDLM handle ldlm enqueued locks that lead to stray locks should a process requesting a lock die before the lock is granted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Vitaly has a patch in the bugzilla bug that needs to be tested and landed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
